{
  "texts": [
    "It doesn't rely on syntactic features or complex neural models.",
    "SSCL (Shi et al. 2021) introduces self-supervised contrastive learning, featuring an attention-based model with a novel smooth self-attention (SSA) module, high-resolution selective mapping (HRSMap) for efficient aspect assignment, and knowledge distillation techniques to enhance aspect detection.",
    "This task involves extracting opinions and aspects of a product or service separately.",
    "In this example, the opinion is \"great,\" and the aspect of \"battery life.\"",
    "AOCE task is often tackled as a tokenclass problem (Yu et al. 2018), where either two label sets are utilized to extract aspect and opinion terms separately, or a unified label set (Wu et al. 2020a; Wang and Pan 2018) is utilized to extract both sentiment elements simultaneously."
  ]
}